cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS 

The paper deals with reinforcement learning with value function approximation, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the exploration-exploitation trade-off in reinforcement learning, which is a key challenge in the field. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also deals with control problems, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) and it involves the use of algorithms, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
